# Ollama on Lenovo ThinkPad T14 Gen 1
**Device:** sixer-ThinkPad-T14-Gen-1 | **OS:** Ubuntu 24.04.4 LTS  
**CPU:** Intel Core i5-10210U (8 threads) | **RAM:** 24 GB | **Disk:** 1.0 TB  
**GPU:** Intel UHD 620 (integrated — no dedicated VRAM)

---

## Hardware Considerations

Since this machine has **no discrete GPU**, Ollama runs entirely on **CPU + system RAM**.

- ✅ 24 GB RAM is generous — enough to run models up to ~14B comfortably
- ⚠️ No GPU acceleration — inference is slower than a dedicated GPU setup
- ✅ 8 CPU threads help parallelise inference
- ❌ Avoid models above 14B — they will be painfully slow

**Rule of thumb:** At 4-bit quantisation (Q4_K_M), a model needs roughly **0.7 GB per billion parameters**.  
- 3B model → ~2–3 GB RAM  
- 8B model → ~5–6 GB RAM  
- 14B model → ~9–10 GB RAM  

