## Recommended Models for This Machine

### 🚀 Fastest — Near-Instant Responses

```bash
ollama run qwen3:0.6b        # ~1 GB RAM  — fastest possible, good for quick tasks
ollama run gemma3:1b         # ~1 GB RAM  — Google's compact model, surprisingly capable
```

**Use when:** You want fast completions, quick Q&A, or are running other heavy apps simultaneously.

---

### ⚡ Sweet Spot — Speed + Quality (Recommended)

```bash
ollama run llama3.2:3b       # ~2–3 GB RAM — great balance, snappy on this CPU
ollama run phi4-mini         # ~3 GB RAM   — Microsoft's efficient small model
```

**Use when:** General assistant tasks, writing help, summarisation, light coding.

---

### 🧠 Best Quality — Still Comfortable

```bash
ollama run llama3.1:8b       # ~5–6 GB RAM — best all-rounder for this hardware
ollama run qwen3:8b          # ~5–6 GB RAM — strong at coding and reasoning
ollama run gemma3:9b         # ~6 GB RAM   — excellent instruction following
```

**Use when:** Coding assistance, document summarisation, more complex reasoning tasks.

---

### 💪 Push It — Slower but More Capable

```bash
ollama run qwen3:14b         # ~9–10 GB RAM — noticeable slowdown, but high quality
ollama run phi4:14b          # ~9–10 GB RAM — strong at math and reasoning
```

**Use when:** You have time to wait and need higher quality output. Expect ~2–5 tokens/sec on this CPU.

---

### ❌ Avoid on This Machine

| Model Size | Why |
|---|---|
| 32B+ | Will use 20+ GB RAM, run at <1 token/sec |
| Any model with GPU layers | No discrete GPU to offload to |

