## Performance Tips

### 1. Set Thread Count Explicitly
The i5-10210U has 4 cores / 8 threads. Tell Ollama to use them all:

```bash
OLLAMA_NUM_THREADS=8 ollama run llama3.1:8b
```

Or set it permanently in `/etc/environment`:
```
OLLAMA_NUM_THREADS=8
```

### 2. Keep RAM Free
Close Chrome tabs and other heavy apps before running larger models. With 24 GB, you have plenty of headroom, but it still helps.

### 3. Use Quantised Models (Default)
Ollama pulls Q4_K_M quantisation by default — this is the best trade-off between quality and speed/RAM for CPU-only setups. Don't pull full-precision (fp16) models.

### 4. Monitor Performance
```bash
# Watch CPU and RAM usage during inference
htop

# Or just RAM usage
free -h
```

